##Who supports the special menstrual needs of frontline female health care workers?

Weixin Signal Wowjiemian

Function introduction, the interface news is China has the influence original financial and economic new media, only serves the independent thinking crowd

Source: MAPWORM

Journalist: Lu Yibei Editor: Zan Hui Fang

”

Protective clothing to wear off a waste, in order to save materials, Wuhan War Epidemic Front doctors and nurses can only seven or eight hours without going to the toilet, is not "hold" or rely on diapers emergency response. For Women's health care, if the encounter of the menstrual period, also can only bear the head.

A female doctor in Wuhan told the interface news that it was a helpless embarrassment to change sanitary articles because of the inconvenience of wearing and taking off protective clothing. In such cases, diapers are used instead, and after four to six hours in the quarantine zone, they are changed together when the protective clothing is changed.

The head of the Propaganda Department at Wuhan No. 3 Hospital also told interface news that the hospital's nurses work four-hour shifts and use diapers if they are menstruating or going to the toilet. In addition, some patients also have this need. New Crown Pneumonia sometimes causes diarrhea, and there are many female patients in the hospital, there is no way to buy Sanitary Napkins. The good news is that some people have donated Adult diaper and safety pants to the hospital.

However, not all medical personnel or patients can use materials such as diapers, a number of Wuhan first-line doctors and nurses told interface news that such materials will be given priority to special groups in special times.

Even diapers are in short supply, not to mention tampons. So what do female health care workers do when they have their periods? Why don't you hear about this kind of help?

Weibo user@liangyustacey shared this concern when she posted on Feb. 7 that Booven wanted to donate sanitary pads and safety pants to female health care workers, asking for advice from netizens. While many people have posted comments discussing the feasibility, some have also asked, "what kind of safety pants should I donate now? Do Doctors and nurses need them? What I need more is a mask and protective clothing. ".

But demand does exist, and the gap is huge.

Not only female medical staff, female patients are also very much in need of menstrual supplies. On@liang Yustacey's Weibo Account, a number of female doctors and nurses left messages saying that the menstrual period was really troublesome, that they had to endure physical pain to continue to hold down their posts, and that they did not even have any sanitary articles, and had applied to the head nurse for two days without being issued There are also women with pneumonia who ask for help, and need reassuring pants, which don't need to be changed frequently. They say they can't even stand up to go to the toilet, let alone change sanitary Napkins, after lying down for so long.

The number of people and institutions paying attention to these needs is also growing.

Blogger@liang Yustacey has been running a sister campaign since February 7 to support the physical health of female medical staff on the front line, in partnership with charitable foundations.

When she asked a front-line doctor if there was any need, she said she wanted to donate her safety pants. Even, the medical staff that asks for help is Hubei Province not only, the hospital of Henan also has the support that asks her to help sanitary Napkin, safety pants.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Screenshot of Blogger@liang Yu Stacey.

The Shanghai Women's Federation has learned from the medical and health institutions that have fought on the front lines of the epidemic that more than 50 percent of doctors are women and more than 90 percent of frontline nurses are women. This also means that more than half of the medical staff on the front line may have a need for menstrual supplies.

However, in Wuhan, where epidemic prevention materials are in short supply, the importance of women's menstrual period supplies can not be compared with life-saving materials such as protective clothing and face masks. The front line of the fight against the epidemic every minute is very tense, medical staff in the inventory of materials, only close to the most people need access.

Noting the related needs, on January 31, the Shanghai Municipal Women's Federation and other women's social organizations issued an initiative to collect related materials and funds, such as safety pants, and all donated items will be donated to the female staff of the Shanghai medical team to Wuhan, municipal Public Health Clinical Center, Municipal Center for Disease Control and Prevention, as well as the city 110 fever clinic first-line female medical staff. By the afternoon of February 2, with the strong support and wide participation of all parties, the total number of Koalas (pants-shaped Sanitary Napkins) raised reached 109,400 pieces, raising 477,600 yuan.

A number of caring merchants on tmall have also donated nearly 400,000 pieces of Adult diaper pants in an emergency. The first batch of supplies left on February 10, a relevant public relations official told interface news, will be sent to the University People's Hospital, Tianyou Hospital, Tongji Hospital, Wuhan Hankou Hospital, Wuhan five hospitals, 8 hospitals.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Caring materials are being distributed. Source: Alibaba

Sanitary Napkin manufacturers have also stepped up to donate their stocks.

On Feb. 1, P & G noticed that Adult diaper and trouser pads were becoming a necessity for frontline female health care workers, the company told interface news. By February 7, the company's Hushubao brand had donated 650 boxes of adult pants to the Shanghai medical team and its aid hospital through the China Youth Foundation and the one foundation, they also donated 1,000 boxes of adult trousers and Koalas (Sanitary Napkins) to six hospitals in Wuhan and Suizhou, Hubei Province, and the Hubei University Medical Aid team.

Xu Youjie, VICE PRESIDENT OF P & G Greater China, told interface news that 650 cases of Adult diaper had been successfully sent to Mount Hua Hospital, Zhongshan Hospital and Huanggang Hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
P & G supplies. Source: P & G Supplies

Blogger@liang Yustacey's "sister campaign peace of mind" continues. As of February 10, a total of 3,317 boxes of safety pants, 3,120 pairs of women's disposable underwear, 2,880 pieces of sanitary Napkins and 700 pieces of hand cream were donated to 26 hospitals in Wuhan, Huanggang, Xiaogan and Ezhou.

When contacted by interface news, Stacey said she and the rest of the volunteers had all gone to war and were really busy. In the four days since February 7, Stacey has slept just 11 hours and lost 4 pounds.

She once wrote on Weibo that the donation of safety pants should not be my hard work, nor should it be the charity fund of any Social Organization, which should have been classified as a "state of war" for the unified procurement and distribution of essential materials, the capacity of individuals and other institutions is too limited. Not only this time the medical staff needs, but also female police officers, female firefighters, female soldiers and so on. She hopes this focus will make the issue of menstrual products for women workers a matter of legitimate concern.
